@database IconClass
@index "Classes.guide/Main"

@Node Main "RxMUI - Icon Class"


Icon class    @{"Index" link "Classes.guide/Main"} @{"Super" link "AreaClass.guide/Main"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Icon class is a subclass of Area class and it is used to
  display icons.

  Of course, you may give an Icon object a Frame, a Background
  and an Inputmode, to make it act like an image button.

  Icon is a subclass of Icon.mcc so you must have Icon.mcc in
  MUI:Libs/MUI to use it. Icon.mcc is copyright of Russell
  Leighton.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}DefaultTool@{fg text}
  S G

  @{fg shine}Name@{fg text}
  S I IND
  The name of an icon without .info

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  None defined

@EndNode
